      {
        "id": 3389432,
        "name": "Ilkka |_ |_| mme",
        "username": "IlkkaL",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/ilkkal/{size}/2504_2.png",
        "created_at": "2022-04-09T18:22:07.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I\u2019m not one to mess around with the thread titles to get people to click but here I almost did it. This an absolutely stupendous bottle of white Burg and just just ridiculous value for money but really when discussing its merits there is no need to even talk about the price. I know William Kelley has sung the praises of this producer but other than that I don\u2019t think there is a lot of talk out there. One of those names people would rather keep a secret as long as possible? I can totally understand that and will do my best to find more wines from this address while the wines remain cheap.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<strong>2014 Jean-Marc Vincent Santenay Les Potets Blanc</strong> <em>- France, Burgundy, C\u00f4te de Beaune, Santenay (9.4.2022)</em><br>\nIntense, expressive and super detailed on the nose with notes of tangy lemon, crushed rock, gun flint, iodine and a kiss of oak. Chablis-esque in its expession and savory, borderline haunting. On the palate extremely youthful with a very firm mouthfeel and high laser-like acidity. Little to no fat with an altogether savory flavor profile. Absolutely great tension with enough flesh to not be one bit austere. Somewhat restrained in its expression and all the better for it. The use of oak is masterful, you can sense that it is there but it has integrated perfectly. Just crystalline stuff, absolutely top notch for the appellation I reckon. Impeccably balanced all the way to the zesty finish and massively drinkable, it is very hard to take long breaks between sips. Wow.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>Posted from <a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">CellarTracker</a></em></p>",
