        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group quote-modified\" data-post=\"9\" data-topic=\"178469\">\n<blockquote>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group quote-modified\" data-post=\"7\" data-topic=\"178469\">\n<blockquote>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"3\" data-topic=\"178469\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>Just wait until you taste Jean-Marc\u2019s 2020s, they are his best wines to date and set a new standard for Santenay.</p>\n<p>Typical of his approach, he is taking advantage of his newfound notoriety to extend \u00e9levage and establish new high density plantings.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I found this one already quite perfect for my palate so hard to see how it could get any better but I guess I\u2019ll need to find out.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I\u2019m on a hiatus from buying wine (and potentiallybreaking it). I if you are to pick any of his non-gravitas reds to buy for 2020, which would you choose?</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Not sure if you were asking me or William but I hope its the latter - I am yet to taste any red from Vincent.</p>",
